<HEADLINE>
FT  05 OCT 93 / World Commodities Prices: Tea
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Landed demand was very strong throughout, reports the Tea Broker's
Association. North Indian teas met keen competition with coloury mediums
often 4 to 8p dearer and selected quality types again a good feature. East
Africans were very well supported with brighter liquoring sorts 10 to 15p
higher, sometimes more, mediums 5 to 10p up. Ceylons sold readily, advancing
10 to 15p. Offshore continuing strong enquiry with prices 5 to 15p up.
Quotations quality 200p/kg, good medium 135p/kg, medium 125p/kg, low medium
100p/kg. The highest price realised this week was 255p/kp for an assam pd.
