FT  05 OCT 93 / Observer: Backlog
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Light at last on one of the mysteries of British Rail's operations - why,
whenever it alters its running schedules, the new timetables are never
available to travellers until after the changes have been put into force.
Asking the question at a suburban ticket office, a reader was told: 'It's
the timetables department; they work to a 25-hour clock.'
