FT  05 OCT 93 / Leisure group trial sent to crown court
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN MASON, Law Courts Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE prosecution of six people following the Serious Fraud Office
investigation into European Leisure, the entertainment and nightclub group,
was yesterday transferred to the crown court by Bow Street magistrates.
The SFO investigation, carried out with the Metropolitan police, centred on
European Leisure's hostile takeover of Midsummer Leisure, the pubs and
discos group, in May 1990.
The six include Mr Michael Ward, former chairman and chief executive of
European Leisure and two former directors, Mr Jeremy Howarth and Mr George
Hendry.
They are charged with conspiracy to defraud, conspiring to create a false
market in the company's shares and theft. All six were remanded on bail.
