FT  05 OCT 93 / World Trade News: CDollars 130m aircraft deal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS and CANUTE JAMES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL, KINGSTON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
BOMBARDIER'S Short Brothers subsidiary in Belfast will supply 20 Sherpa C-23
aircraft worth CDollars 130m (Pounds 64m) to the American armed forces, for
delivery over the next three years. The US has taken options on 10 more.
Bombardier has won a USDollars 127m (Pounds 82.4m) order for six
