FT  05 OCT 93 / Taiwan expects 6% growth rate
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TAIPEI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Taiwan's annual economic growth is expected to slow to an average 6 per cent
in the five years up to 1997 as the island's export-led boom cools down,
according to the government's Bureau of Statistics, Reuter reports from
Taipei.
'Slower growth will be mainly due to curbs on government spending, which is
expected to show zero growth in real terms, compared with an average 8.9 per
cent in the previous five years,' a bureau official said yesterday.
Gross national product expanded at an annual rate of 10 per cent in 1983-87
and 6.7 per cent in 1988-92. Between 1952 and 1990 it grew at an average of
nearly 9 per cent.
