FT  04 OCT 93 / Observer: Corker
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Whilst lunching alone at a restaurant near the House of Commons, shadow
industry spokesman Robin Cook was interrupted in his musings by the arrival
of a bottle of fine wine at his table. Its provenance?
A man sitting nearby promptly introduced himself as a director of a company
recently acquired by Anglo-American conglomerate Hanson.
Infuriated by what he saw as the new owner's policy of cutting investment,
he had naturally relished the opportunity to wine, if not dine, the senior
Labour figure - at the expense of one of the Tory party's more generous
donors.
