FT  04 OCT 93 / People: Christies' board acquires a French style
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Nicholas Clive Worms has been appointed a non-executive director of
Christies International and chairman of Christie's France.
He is senior partner of Worms &amp; Cie, one of France's more venerable
financial services and industrial companies, having been established by his
great-great grandfather in the turbulent year of 1848.
Worms has long taken a personal interest in the art market. He has a swathe
of directorships in French companies, including the consumer goods producer
BSN and the television station TF1.
Sir Anthony Tennant, chairman of Christies International, said that he would
be 'a very valuable addition' to the board.
