<HEADLINE>
FT  04 OCT 93 / World News in Brief: US soldiers die as Somali rebels down
helicopters
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
At least five soldiers died when two US helicopters were shot down during a
UN operation in the capital, Mogadishu, against rebel Somali forces of
warlord Mohamed Farah Aideed. Other US troops were reported wounded in the
operation, during which 20 rebels were arrested.
